## Phase 0 — Scope & data access
- Name the **economic buyer** and the **ops owner**. No deployment without both.
- Inventory the systems: which ERP / supplier-net / mail / sheets dialect the customer runs
  → this sets the four `*_SYSTEM` values (already stamped above; re-stamp with `{{GENERATOR}} {{SLUG}} --erp … --supplier …` if wrong).
- Secure data access **and consent**. Domain data is family-held / off-device — the constraint is access/consent, not ML.
- **Gate:** signed scope + read access to all four system classes; each SaaS dialect chosen and validated against its allowlist.

## Phase 1 — Deployment stamp  *(this artifact)*
- `{{GENERATOR}} {{SLUG}}` copied the exception board + ROI report verbatim, stamped `.mcp.json`
  with the chosen dialects, and seeded `roi-baseline.json` + `roi/ops_baseline.jsonl` + `roi/ops_automated.jsonl`.
- Inject `{{APPROVAL_TOKEN_VAR}}` into the **host env only** (`.local/connector-config.env`), never VCS.
- **Gate:** `just check` / `just smoke` green in the kit (staged-write proof — corpus fingerprint byte-identical before/after approve+execute); `active_system()` reports the intended dialect on all four servers; approvals **fail closed** with no token.

## Phase 2 — Policy authoring  *(the FDE's core act)*
- Open `exception-spec.inkspec.html`. Author tolerances, decision rules (condition → action →
  terminal), exception paths and exceptions-of-exceptions, hand-to-human fallbacks, the chase
  ladder, UOM, audit fields, and per-customer overrides. Replace every `<<TOKEN>>` with the
  customer's real value.
- Export `policy.json` into `fixtures/retail_ops/policy.json` (Strict = the ten loader keys;
  Carry = the ten keys + `_exception_spec`, both load unchanged).
- **Gate:** clean export — no *BLOCKS EXPORT* marks; Strict-mode export shape-identical to the
  committed fixture; `frozenset(gated_actions) == rules.GATED_ACTIONS` (the frozen 11 —
  `pay_invoice, issue_debit_note, issue_credit_note, post_deduction, accept_chargeback,
  po_amendment, po_cancellation, accept_over_ship, authorize_return, commit_supplier_payment,
  override_scorecard`; `write_off` / `close_exception` must **not** be in the list); each of
  the four hand-to-human classes has a fallback.

## Phase 3 — Baseline & shadow-run
- Fill `roi-baseline.json` with **re-sourced** customer scalars (all eleven `params` + two
  `targets`; only `.value` is read by `roi.py`).
- Capture 6–8 weeks of real BEFORE data into `roi/ops_baseline.jsonl` (per-week `MARKER_WK##`),
  replacing the seeded rows.
- Run the agent in read/shadow — staged writes only, nothing approved.
- **Gate:** shadow disposition matches human disposition within the agreed error bar; false-exception rate under threshold; ROI baseline signed by the buyer.

## Phase 4 — Gated go-live
- Enable staged writes with a human `approve()` in the loop. Humans hold `{{APPROVAL_TOKEN_VAR}}`
  and decide run-vs-wait per pending approval.
- **Gate:** every mutation traverses stage → human-approve; audit record complete over
  `audit_required_fields`; **zero auto-execution** (structural — the agent cannot hold the token).

## Phase 5 — Value proof
- Fill `roi/ops_automated.jsonl` with real AFTER data (true-vs-false labeled). Run the ROI
  harness; present the honest waterfall in `roi/roi-report.inkspec.html`:
  `correct_auto_rate` beside raw `auto_resolution_rate`; net-touches-saved **after** false-positive
  docking (`A_correct×t_manual − A_false×t_rework − F_detect×t_review`); deduction $ recovered;
  OTIF lift × `otif_attribution_alpha`; weeks-to-breakeven vs. `targets`.
- **Gate:** computed net value positive and reconciled to the buyer's ledger; time-to-value within the committed window.

## Phase 6 — Expansion  *(land-and-expand)*
Widen scope along the cheapest axis first:
1. more suppliers / SKUs on the same dialects,
2. new system dialect (flip a `*_SYSTEM` value — no code change),
3. additional exception classes in the board (the `_exception_spec` carry layer feeds a future data-driven `compute.py`),
4. additional sites / business units → **re-stamp with a new slug** (`{{GENERATOR}} <new-slug>`).
- **Gate per increment:** re-run Phases 2–5 on the delta; drift-guard and fingerprint invariants stay green; each expansion re-proves ROI before the next.

